article.description: Tilman Dunbar scored 15 points and made 9 of 10 free throws and Navy rallied late to beat Loyola (Md) 60-52 Wednesday night to take sole possession of second place in the Patriot League behind Bu
article.headline: Navy rallies to beat Loyola (Md) 60-52 behind Dunbar
article.linkText: Navy rallies to beat Loyola (Md) 60-52 behind Dunbar
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Tilman Dunbar scored 15 points and made 9 of 10 free throws and Navy rallied late to beat Loyola (Md) 60-52 Wednesday night to take sole possession of second place in the Patriot League behind Bucknell. Jace Hogan added 10 points and Will Kelly had six blocks for the Midshipmen (13-5, 4-1), who made 23 of 35 free throws and trailed 26-22 at halftime. Dunbar's two free throws amid a 13-0 run tied it at 42 with 5:15 to go and Navy led 49-42 after Shawn Anderson's jumper with 1:41 left. Andre Walker scored five-straight points to pull Loyola within 58-52 with seven seconds left, but Dunbar iced the game with two more free throws. Walker finished with 15 points and had five steals, and Eric Laster scored 13 points and Tyler Hubbard had 11. Loyola (4-12, 3-2) committed 30 fouls.
